  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can I do SEO for AngularJS based sites?",
  "response": "Yes, you can perform SEO for AngularJS-based sites, but there are extra considerations because AngularJS is a JavaScript framework that dynamically generates content on the client side. Search engine crawlers may not be able to fully render or index the dynamic content without additional techniques. Here are some strategies:\n\n1. **Server-Side Rendering (SSR)**: Implementing SSR can help search engines crawl your site more effectively because the content is rendered on the server before being sent to the client. This means the HTML content will be available to search engine bots when they access the site.\n\n2. **Pre-rendering**: Tools like Prerender.io can be used to create static HTML snapshots of your pages for search engines while still using AngularJS for dynamic functionalities. These snapshots are served to bots, ensuring they can index the content properly.\n\n3. **Meta Tags and SEO-friendly URLs**: Just like traditional SEO, ensure you are using proper meta tags, titles, descriptions, and SEO-friendly URLs. Angular's router can be configured to use clean URLs without hash fragments.\n\n4. **Angular Universal**: If you are using a more modern version of Angular, Angular Universal is a built-in solution for server-side rendering and pre-rendering, which makes it easier to manage SEO in more recent Angular applications.\n\n5. **Structured Data**: Implementing structured data (JSON-LD, schema.org) can also help search engines understand the content and purpose of your pages better.\n\n6. **Dynamic Rendering**: Google supports dynamic rendering, which means you can serve different content to users and bots. For example, you can use tools like Puppeteer to render the content for bots.\n\n7. **Lazy Loading and Code Splitting**: While these techniques improve performance, be cautious to ensure that search engine crawlers can still access all your content.\n\n8. **Backlinks and Social Signals**: Gaining quality backlinks and social signals can improve the site's authority, which is crucial for SEO. Ensure they are pointing to your main content.\n\nRemember, SEO for JavaScript-heavy sites can be more complex than traditional HTML sites, but it's definitely achievable with the right techniques and tools. Effective SEO requires regular monitoring and adjustments based on the search engines' evolving capabilities to render JavaScript.",
